    {
      "id": "bb90beb6719e038527f721b5e5873deeff58f536",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2022-08-23 17:53:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Shaun,\n\nKarsten Weiss added two comments related to this patch in LU-16006:\n\n1) dkms: did you see Knut Franke's patch attached to LU-16015? FWIW: This patch is what I used to build both Lustre 2.12.9 and 2.15.1 with ZFS successfully using dkms-3.0.3 on CentOS 7.9 and Rocky Linux 8.6 respectively.\n\n2) kmod: Wouldn't it be cleaner to remove the (wrong/unnecessary) kmod-lustre-osd-zfs requirement of lustre-osd-zfs-mount on a DKMS build (i.e. making the Requires conditional) instead of adding the fake provides? The latter could be confusing as a kmod-lustre-osd-zfs rpm actually exists. (See Nathanial Clark's comment in LU-15976)\n\nCould you please advise?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2da82aab637c904cf346371ea63a19bbb99fbde1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 808,
        "name": "Shaun Tancheff",
        "email": "shaun.tancheff@hpe.com",
        "username": "stancheff"
      },
      "date": "2022-08-24 14:36:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(4 comments)\n\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/48083/ has been updated.\n\n> dkms: did you see Knut Franke's patch attached to LU-16015?\n\nI had not looked at the patch.\nThe filter \"| sort -V | head -n1\" does make sense to include.\n\n> kmod: Wouldn't it be cleaner to remove the (wrong/unnecessary)\n> kmod-lustre-osd-zfs requirement of lustre-osd-zfs-mount on a\n? DKMS build (i.e. making the Requires conditional) instead of\n> adding the fake provides? The latter could be confusing as a\n> kmod-lustre-osd-zfs rpm actually exists. (See Nathanial Clark's comment in LU-15976)\n\nSince the dkms packages is providing all the files and support\nof the packages then it is best to report that it is providing\nthe package. The prevents (for example) someone accidentally\ninstalling the package 'lustre-osd-zfs-mount' and then uninstalling\nthe package and thus breaking the lustre-zfs-dkms package.\n\nBy providing the package the duplicate install is prevented.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
